          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The ratio C fossil/C biogenic has been estimated to 50:50 using data concerning global material uses and mass flows (J.K. Steinberger et al., Ecological Economics, 2010, 69:1148–1158). Repartition of different fossil fuels was estimated using production volumes in ecoinvent v3.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6393c14b-db78-445d-a47b-c0cb866a1b25" amount="0.224356043320127" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The following substances were considered to represent AOX: trichloromethane (chloroform), chlorophenols, chlorobenzenes, dioxins and furans (EEA).
The ratio C fossil/C biogenic has been estimated to 50:50 using data concerning global material uses and mass flows (J.K. Steinberger et al., Ecological Economics, 2010, 69:1148–1158). Repartition of different fossil fuels was estimated using production volumes in ecoinvent v3.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="3a0af1d6-04c3-41c6-a3da-92c4f61e0eaa" amount="1.0" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
